1 Existing law sets forth the Nevada Certified Court Reporters’ and Licensed Court
2 Reporting Firms’ Law, which provides for the certification and regulation of certified court
3 reporters and the licensure and regulation of court reporting firms by the Certified Court
4 Reporters’ Board of Nevada. (Chapter 656 of NRS) [Existing law prohibits a person from
5 engaging in the practice of court reporting without a valid certificate of registration as a
6 certified court reporter. (NRS 656.145, 656.300) Sections 3.5, 4.7-10 and 11.5-15 of this bill
7 provide for the certification and regulation by the Board of persons engaged in the “practice of
8 legal recording,” which section 5 defines to mean, in general, the recording of certain
9 proceedings by the use of audio equipment, video cameras or any system of recording
10 simultaneous audio and video. Section 5 designates a person certified by the Board to engage

